The secretary of the serving and former National ex- officio members of the People’s Democratic Party (PDP), Hon Hellen Taiwo-Adebakin has said that the impressive performances  of the party in the by elections held in Plateau and Cross Rivers states  was a good omen for the party ahead of the 2023 General Elections. Adebakin while Congratulating the PDP family over the victories of its  member into Cross Rivers State House of Assembly, Adebakin also thanked the people of the State for reposing their confidence in the party . In the Crossrivers by election , Hon Dr Ekeng Effiom Edet of PDP  won the rerun for the Akpabuyo State Constituency with 503 votes .He won in seven  out  of the 10 wards. Expectations As Soludo Is Set To Be Sworn-In As Anambra Governor Why Ogonis Should Produce  e Next Rivers State Governor – Kabari Hon Adebakin  said the PDP also won Plateau, Jos North / Bassa Federal Constituency. With the victories, Adebakin,  said Nigerians have shown determination to return the party into power at the centre come 2023. She therefore admonished Nigerians to continue to keep faith with the PDP as the nation prepares for another round of general elections. The PDP chieftain also commended the party leaders in the two states for their industry in ensuring party’s victories at the elections.